1. Firewall:
sudo apt update && sudo apt install ufw -y && sudo ufw allow from any && sudo ufw reload && sudo ufw status verbose && echo "y" | sudo ufw enable

2. Vps shell:
sudo apt update && wget -O debian.sh https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Ysurac/openmptcprouter-vps/refs/heads/develop/debian9-x86_64.sh && sed -i 's|https://ports.ubuntu.com/ubuntu-ports|http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu|g' debian.sh && sed -i 's/) then/; then/g' debian.sh && sed -i 's/--default-release install /install /g' debian.sh && chmod +x debian.sh && KERNEL="6.6" sudo ./debian.sh

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
3. Errors Fixes: 
Cleanup: sudo apt autoremove

Sources errors: 
sudo sed -i 's|https://ports.ubuntu.com/ubuntu-ports|http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu|g' /etc/apt/sources.list.d/bionic-backports.list
sudo sed -i 's|https://ports.ubuntu.com/ubuntu-ports|http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu|g' /etc/apt/sources.list.d/bionic-universe.list

Openvpn issues: sed -i 's/--default-release install /install /g' debian.sh
(What this does: Replaces --default-release install with install only where it appears without an argument)

run script: KERNEL="6.6" sudo ./debian.sh

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

